  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Conventions\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Egmont Group guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Key Legal Provisions\n- Criminalizing money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture\n- Establishing financial intelligence units\n\n4. Compliance Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n\n5. Enforcement Mechanisms\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Civil penalties\n- International cooperation\n- Financial sanctions\n\n6. Regulatory Oversight\n- Banking regulators\n- Financial crime enforcement agencies\n- Law enforcement collaboration\n\n7. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining financial system integrity.",
